    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - High-pressure Oil Pump - Removal - Branch Tube</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26511.2.4" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Branch Tube</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>To remove the branch tube assembly, the rear cover and cylinder heads must be removed. See the
                    Rear Cover, and Cylinder Head and Valve Train sections.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001213" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11047.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the branch tube bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, take extra care to not drop these bolts. These bolts are not captured
                    within the branch tube.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove a Torx&#174; socket bolt (M6 x 40) from each side of branch tube assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001214" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11048.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the branch tube adapter</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Branch tube adapter bolts (2)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">#10 quick release tool</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect the high-pressure oil pump from the branch tube adapter connection using a #10
                Quick Release Tool. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_259.xml" xrefid="E30012C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001215" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11050.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing the branch tube adapter from the branch tube assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, take extra care to not drop these bolts. These bolts are not captured
                    within the branch tube adapter.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen two bolts (M6 x 30) connecting the branch tube adapter to the branch tube assembly
                and discard O-ring, if not done so already.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
